      • sublist

        public static <T> List<T> sublist​(List<T> list,
                                  int from,
                                  int length)
        Returns a sublist of the provided list starting with starting with element from and containing at most length elements.
        1. If from is negative, it is relative to the end of the list.
        2. If length is negative, the sublist is taken to the left of from (inclusive).
        3. Both from and length are clamped to their minimum and maximum values. In other words you will never get an ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException.
        Parameters:
        list - The List to extract a sublist from
        from - The start index
        length - The length of the substr
        Returns:
